# Compiled claude-rules outputs — managed by "minsky rules compile --target
# claude-rules" (mt#2868), not Prettier. Same single/double-quote conflict as
# .claude/agents/ below: the emitter single-quotes the `paths:` flow-sequence
# so a sanitized `\[` bracket-escape survives YAML round-trip untouched
# (single-quoted YAML scalars have no backslash-escape processing); Prettier's
# markdown formatter rewrites those to double quotes (and would also collapse
# the deliberate lack of a blank line between the closing `---` and the
# generation banner, which matters for the check-generated-file-edit 5-line
# scan window — see claude-rules.ts's module doc). The compile-check guard
# (src/hooks/pre-commit.ts runRulesCompileCheck) owns staleness instead.
.claude/rules/

# Compiled agent outputs — managed by "minsky compile --target claude-agents",
# not Prettier. js-yaml emits single-quoted YAML for comma-containing scalars
# (e.g. `tools: 'Read, Bash'`) which Prettier rewrites to double quotes; the two
# can't both win, so the generator owns the format and the compile-check guard
# (src/hooks/pre-commit.ts runCompileCheck) enforces staleness instead (mt#2497).
.claude/agents/

# Compiled skill outputs — managed by "minsky compile --target claude-skills",
# not Prettier. The compiler emits the source markdown verbatim, so when a source
# uses Prettier-divergent markdown (e.g. `*italic*` vs `_italic_`), lint-staged
# would rewrite the compiled SKILL.md and the compile-check guard
# (src/hooks/pre-commit.ts runCompileCheck) would then flag it STALE — a deadlock
# that blocks the commit (mt#2555). The compile-check guard owns staleness for
# compiled skills instead.
# NOTE: .claude/skills/ is a SHARED output dir — it also holds legacy hand-authored
# SKILL.md files (no .minsky/skills/ source); those are no longer Prettier-checked
# as a side effect of this ignore. Author new skills under .minsky/skills/ (ADR-015).
.claude/skills/